# Typography Consistency (Pages)

Use the following typography and color standards consistently in all page-level UI and page components:

- Parent header (section/page/card top title): `text-xl font-bold text-navy-700 dark:text-white`
- Parent description (text below parent header): `mt-2 text-base text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400`
- Child header (item title/content title under a section): `text-base font-medium text-navy-700 dark:text-white`
- Child description (helper/meta/secondary text under child header): `mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400`Additional notes:- Keep dark mode pairings for all heading/description text.
- For inline action links inside descriptions, use `font-medium text-brand-500 hover:text-brand-500 dark:text-white`.
- Reuse these text levels before introducing other font sizes in page content.
